WEBVTT

00:03.950 --> 00:05.700
Easy to load. Never jams.

00:05.750 --> 00:07.370
Basically point and shoot.

00:07.420 --> 00:09.440
Nice thing about the .38, it
doesn't have too much of a kick.

00:09.490 --> 00:11.210
But don't worry.

00:11.260 --> 00:14.440
Aim it right, it'll get the job done.

00:18.060 --> 00:21.020
Fuck. Fuck.

00:21.070 --> 00:22.690
I don't understand.

00:22.740 --> 00:25.560
I'm so sorry. I'm so sorry.

00:25.610 --> 00:26.560
Hey.

00:26.610 --> 00:29.160
Fuck!

00:29.210 --> 00:31.790
You told me. You said he was "they."

00:31.840 --> 00:34.800
You said God told you.

00:34.850 --> 00:36.830
I tried to call you, man.

00:36.880 --> 00:39.000
You told me to turn off my phone.

00:39.050 --> 00:40.870
You told me not to communicate.

00:40.920 --> 00:42.340
I know, I know. I... I...

00:42.390 --> 00:44.340
Fuck!

00:44.390 --> 00:47.410
Is this innocent blood on my hands?

00:47.460 --> 00:48.460
Is it?

00:50.700 --> 00:54.650
Get the fuck away from me!

00:54.700 --> 00:57.890
I tried to call you.

00:57.940 --> 00:59.590
You stay the fuck away from me.

00:59.640 --> 01:01.560
I tried to call you.

01:01.610 --> 01:05.800
I tried to call you. I
tried to call you, man.

01:07.000 --> 01:13.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:38.780 --> 01:40.600
Josh.

01:43.420 --> 01:45.140
Josh.

02:03.900 --> 02:06.290
Hey, where are you?

02:06.340 --> 02:09.330
You're not going to
believe what I did tonight.

02:09.380 --> 02:11.530
And now I'm hungry for some Top Dog.

02:11.580 --> 02:14.360
So if you want one, you
just got to call me, okay?

02:14.410 --> 02:16.670
Because the window is closing.

02:16.720 --> 02:20.070
And, um, oh, I turned in the note,

02:20.120 --> 02:22.470
and the court date is still on.

02:22.520 --> 02:24.170
So...

02:25.020 --> 02:27.580
Okay, um,

02:27.630 --> 02:30.510
yeah, bye.

03:29.741 --> 03:31.941
<b>Synced and corrected by Caio
www.addic7ed.com</b>

04:16.240 --> 04:17.920
There's a courtroom full of people

04:17.970 --> 04:19.860
waiting for you, Pernell,

04:19.910 --> 04:23.390
including one pissed-off me.

04:28.150 --> 04:30.730
Pernell, we got to get started.

04:33.890 --> 04:35.940
You don't...

04:35.990 --> 04:39.540
see any doves, do you?

04:45.600 --> 04:46.920
Like birds?

05:00.450 --> 05:02.630
I think I'm gonna need a ride.

05:13.530 --> 05:15.110
No, no, no, no, no.

05:15.160 --> 05:17.110
No phone.

05:17.160 --> 05:19.150
How about round three?

05:19.200 --> 05:23.250
Jesus, are you sure?

05:23.300 --> 05:25.720
You barely made it through round two.

05:25.770 --> 05:28.390
Well, feels like round three.

05:30.810 --> 05:32.930
I'll say.

05:41.820 --> 05:43.110
Is that Pernell again?

05:43.160 --> 05:44.910
No, it's Randy.

05:44.960 --> 05:45.910
Don't fall for it.

05:45.960 --> 05:47.310
She's just his beard.

05:47.360 --> 05:49.110
No, you call her back, he'll answer.

05:55.340 --> 05:57.450
Oh, shit.

05:59.340 --> 06:00.960
I got to go.

06:01.010 --> 06:03.130
What?

06:03.180 --> 06:07.060
What could Randy have possibly
said to make you leave?

06:11.920 --> 06:13.440
Ladies and gentlemen, thank you.

06:13.490 --> 06:16.310
10% Day is now in the Renaissance era.

06:16.360 --> 06:20.410
Renaissance. Renaissance era.

06:20.460 --> 06:22.610
- You heard?
- Randy called me.

06:22.660 --> 06:24.150
A week ago he wouldn't take his medicine.

06:24.200 --> 06:25.450
Now he's checking himself
into the crazy house.

06:25.500 --> 06:26.450
What the fuck happened?

06:26.500 --> 06:28.120
I don't know, Bobo.

06:28.170 --> 06:31.520
I haven't been home since I
heard about his recent nuptials.

06:31.570 --> 06:34.320
You left him, now?

06:34.370 --> 06:36.590
I needed space.

06:36.640 --> 06:38.490
And you couldn't move into
one of the other six bedrooms

06:38.540 --> 06:40.000
in the mansion?

06:40.050 --> 06:41.400
You need to go talk to him.

06:41.450 --> 06:43.430
Get him out of there
before people find out.

06:43.480 --> 06:45.230
I'm running a city.

06:45.280 --> 06:47.400
I'm giving a speech at the
Kiwanis Club in two hours.

06:47.450 --> 06:48.740
Can't just drop everything

06:48.790 --> 06:50.110
and look at ink blots with Pernell.

06:50.160 --> 06:51.940
Not gonna be me, Bobo.

06:51.990 --> 06:55.850
I have done everything I could
to keep him in the stable.

06:55.900 --> 06:57.080
I'm out.

06:57.130 --> 06:58.480
Everything but stay home.

06:58.530 --> 07:00.920
- Oh, low blow.
- Okay, okay.

07:00.970 --> 07:03.850
I'm just saying, we've all taken
plenty of hits for the team.

07:03.900 --> 07:06.790
I feel like the fucking first
wave on the beaches at Normandy.

07:06.840 --> 07:09.020
Maybe we leave him in there.

07:13.250 --> 07:14.900
No.

07:14.950 --> 07:18.570
No, not when I'm getting my
concrete pour in a few days.

07:18.620 --> 07:21.540
Maybe when the Brooks deal
is actually set in stone,

07:21.590 --> 07:23.070
then Pernell can go ahead

07:23.120 --> 07:25.840
and play Old MacDonald
at the fucking funny farm,

07:25.890 --> 07:27.240
but right now,

07:27.290 --> 07:29.750
all the work that you and
I have done is at risk.

07:29.800 --> 07:32.520
This is... this is just one
more hurdle we have to get over.

07:32.570 --> 07:34.920
You... you've got to talk to him.

07:34.970 --> 07:37.750
Bobo, I am telling you,

07:37.800 --> 07:40.220
if I see him,

07:40.270 --> 07:42.530
it's gonna make things worse.

07:45.210 --> 07:47.000
Okay, okay.

07:47.050 --> 07:48.700
Okay, it's gonna have to be tomorrow,

07:48.750 --> 07:51.770
but I'll take care of it.

07:51.820 --> 07:53.200
Where's he staying at, again?

07:53.250 --> 07:55.710
Serenity Lake.

07:55.760 --> 07:57.640
Maybe when you get there,
you can talk to somebody

07:57.690 --> 07:59.610
about your blood pressure.

08:14.240 --> 08:16.090
I thought there'd be a nice view.

08:16.140 --> 08:19.290
Like at Passages?

08:19.340 --> 08:21.160
That's bullshit.

08:21.210 --> 08:23.530
You're out on some bluff.
You're looking out at the ocean.

08:23.580 --> 08:26.000
You're thinking, "Things
can't be that bad."

08:26.050 --> 08:27.600
Well, fuck that.

08:27.650 --> 08:30.440
Things are that bad, and
that's why you're here.

08:30.490 --> 08:32.909
You want a vacation, you go to Passages.

08:32.960 --> 08:35.140
You want to work, you come here.

08:38.200 --> 08:39.919
I'm here.

08:39.970 --> 08:42.750
I know.

08:42.799 --> 08:44.790
So what do you want?

08:45.970 --> 08:49.220
I've been...

08:49.270 --> 08:51.090
having hallucinations.

08:51.140 --> 08:52.600
So you said at intake.

08:52.650 --> 08:55.230
You've been hearing voices too.

08:55.280 --> 08:57.130
But what do you want?

08:57.180 --> 08:59.370
Or did you just come here
to get that off your chest?

08:59.420 --> 09:02.270
I want them gone.

09:02.320 --> 09:04.540
There's an answer.

09:04.590 --> 09:06.710
Next question.

09:06.760 --> 09:09.210
What's causing them?

09:09.260 --> 09:11.910
- I don't know.
- Bullshit.

09:11.960 --> 09:14.250
- Excuse me?
- You're full of shit.

09:14.300 --> 09:16.120
It's not schizophrenia.

09:16.170 --> 09:17.890
That shit doesn't kick
in for the first time

09:17.940 --> 09:20.190
when you're old enough to be a grandpa.

09:20.240 --> 09:22.930
Something happened,

09:22.980 --> 09:25.500
and I know you didn't just
ship in from Afghanistan,

09:25.550 --> 09:28.230
so what the fuck?

09:28.280 --> 09:30.570
I don't appreciate the
tone you're taking with me.

09:30.620 --> 09:32.640
Well, then take a swing.

09:35.590 --> 09:38.370
I'm kidding. I don't want to fight.

09:38.420 --> 09:41.210
And I also don't want to
waste your time either.

09:41.260 --> 09:44.610
Most places will dose you with
pills they don't understand

09:44.660 --> 09:47.120
or let you cry on a couch for a decade.

09:47.170 --> 09:48.820
I don't go that way.

09:48.870 --> 09:52.820
If you don't want real talk, then walk.

09:56.240 --> 09:59.700
I thought it was God sending me messages.

10:02.820 --> 10:04.300
So for the last few months,

10:04.350 --> 10:06.870
you thought you were talking to the Divine.

10:08.620 --> 10:10.970
And now?

10:13.790 --> 10:17.150
I just... think I'm crazy.

10:18.760 --> 10:20.320
What changed?

10:25.140 --> 10:26.690
My client's already
answered these questions.

10:26.740 --> 10:29.590
It's okay. Whatever it takes to find Josh.

10:29.640 --> 10:31.890
I called him a hundred times.

10:31.940 --> 10:34.260
I called all of his friends,
and nobody's heard from him.

10:34.310 --> 10:36.700
And how long have you two
been seeing each other?

10:36.750 --> 10:38.370
We're not seeing each other.

10:38.420 --> 10:40.640
I moved with him because I
didn't want to stay in my house.

10:40.690 --> 10:42.970
But if he did go away for some reason,

10:43.020 --> 10:44.510
you'd expect him to be in touch.

10:44.560 --> 10:45.680
Absolutely.

10:45.730 --> 10:47.210
This is not like him.

10:47.260 --> 10:48.310
People can surprise you.

10:48.360 --> 10:51.010
We had this guy go missing for three days.

10:51.060 --> 10:52.780
He had a wife and three kids.

10:52.830 --> 10:54.120
Turns out he drove to Denver

10:54.170 --> 10:55.650
because the Broncos made the Super Bowl,

10:55.700 --> 10:57.650
and he had to stand in line for tickets.

10:57.700 --> 10:59.890
Phone died. Didn't want to get out of line.

10:59.940 --> 11:01.660
You think she's overreacting?

11:01.710 --> 11:04.660
I'm not overreacting.
Something's not right.

11:04.710 --> 11:06.070
I think it's also worth mentioning

11:06.110 --> 11:07.750
that one of the last people Josh was with

11:07.780 --> 11:10.300
before she lost contact
with him was Pernell Harris.

11:14.090 --> 11:15.200
Is that right?

11:15.250 --> 11:18.270
Yeah, Josh texted me that he was there,

11:18.320 --> 11:20.520
but I don't know that that
had anything to do with this.

11:20.530 --> 11:21.680
But we do know the only way Pernell

11:21.730 --> 11:23.750
keeps his son on life support

11:23.800 --> 11:25.950
is if Josh Miller doesn't testify in court.

11:28.270 --> 11:31.390
You think Judge Harris paid
Josh to disappear for a while?

11:31.440 --> 11:32.620
Maybe.

11:32.670 --> 11:34.090
But because of that connection,

11:34.140 --> 11:36.360
we should make this a
priority, don't you think?

11:39.080 --> 11:40.960
So we don't even know Mr. Miller's missing.

11:41.010 --> 11:44.200
He's got his car, his
car keys, and his phone.

11:44.250 --> 11:45.770
When people go missing,
the first thing we look for

11:45.820 --> 11:47.500
is something they'd never leave behind.

11:47.550 --> 11:49.470
I'm here.

11:49.520 --> 11:52.440
He wouldn't just disappear
without telling me.

12:13.110 --> 12:14.110
Ah.

13:33.490 --> 13:34.980
I'm not angry with you.

13:35.030 --> 13:37.050
I was gonna tell you.

13:37.100 --> 13:40.280
You were just trying
to find the right time.

13:43.140 --> 13:46.360
Maybe there isn't a right time.

13:48.310 --> 13:51.630
It still would have been
good to hear it from you.

13:51.680 --> 13:53.860
I know.

13:55.680 --> 13:57.300
I'm sorry.

13:59.950 --> 14:02.270
I guess you have a decision to make.

14:03.560 --> 14:05.340
We.

14:11.130 --> 14:13.950
It's your body, Alicia.

14:14.000 --> 14:16.350
But it's our baby.

14:31.080 --> 14:32.800
The procedure went as planned,

14:32.850 --> 14:34.200
but I don't want to get your hopes up.

14:34.250 --> 14:35.940
There's been a lot of cranial damage,

14:35.990 --> 14:38.940
but we'll know more once
the swelling goes down.

14:38.990 --> 14:40.910
Thank you.

14:43.860 --> 14:45.410
What did the doctor say?

14:45.460 --> 14:49.150
They had to operate to relieve
the swelling in his brain.

14:54.940 --> 14:57.590
How are you holding up?

14:57.640 --> 14:59.630
Oh.

15:00.950 --> 15:04.170
It's okay. It's okay.

15:05.550 --> 15:09.170
Hey, we're a family,

15:09.220 --> 15:12.980
and we're gonna get
through this like a family,

15:13.030 --> 15:16.210
and we're gonna be by PJ's
side until he wakes up.

15:20.300 --> 15:22.890
Do you want to go see him now?

15:22.940 --> 15:24.020
No, it's okay.

15:24.070 --> 15:26.260
You go. He needs you.

15:26.310 --> 15:30.430
I'll stay here with his mother.

15:30.480 --> 15:32.330
Oh.

15:38.650 --> 15:40.670
You should go in there.

15:40.720 --> 15:42.440
One of the nurses said that

15:42.490 --> 15:43.870
patients recover faster

15:43.920 --> 15:44.870
if the family spends time with them.

15:44.920 --> 15:46.910
I'm not going in there.

15:46.960 --> 15:49.340
What?

15:49.390 --> 15:52.150
PJ doesn't want to recover.

15:56.570 --> 15:57.390
That's your son in there.

15:57.440 --> 16:00.190
My son shot himself in the head.

16:00.240 --> 16:03.090
He wants to die, so let him.

16:08.350 --> 16:11.900
So your son's
life hung in the balance,

16:11.950 --> 16:15.140
and you said, "Let him die."

16:15.190 --> 16:17.070
How long did it take you
to regret saying that?

16:17.120 --> 16:20.010
The minute it came out of my mouth.

16:21.790 --> 16:22.740
I didn't mean it.

16:22.790 --> 16:24.180
You didn't mean it?

16:24.230 --> 16:27.720
Or you didn't mean to say it?

16:27.770 --> 16:29.450
I was angry.

16:29.500 --> 16:31.790
Hey, I get it.

16:31.840 --> 16:33.360
If someone had shot PJ in the head,

16:33.410 --> 16:36.060
you would hate that fuck
for the rest of your life.

16:36.110 --> 16:39.690
Unfortunately, in this case,
that fuck happened to be PJ.

16:39.740 --> 16:42.100
No.

16:42.150 --> 16:43.670
I was angry at the world.

16:43.720 --> 16:45.940
I just...

16:45.990 --> 16:48.240
I just took it out on PJ.

16:49.990 --> 16:51.770
Okay, let's go back.

16:51.820 --> 16:54.340
Anger is a by-product of fear.

16:54.390 --> 16:56.650
What were you afraid of?

16:59.760 --> 17:01.020
Losing PJ, I guess.

17:01.070 --> 17:03.450
You guess? That's it?

17:03.500 --> 17:06.089
He's my son. Isn't that enough?

17:06.140 --> 17:07.520
Not even close.

17:07.569 --> 17:09.260
A lot of people lose loved
ones, even their kids.

17:09.310 --> 17:11.630
They don't wind up swimming in a fountain

17:11.680 --> 17:14.099
convinced they have God on speed dial.

17:21.720 --> 17:24.740
But this is a good start.

17:24.790 --> 17:26.440
You want these hallucinations to go away,

17:26.490 --> 17:29.210
you need to figure out
what you're afraid of.

17:34.530 --> 17:35.820
Where's my coffee?

17:35.870 --> 17:38.450
It's in the café. The
line was long as hell.

17:38.500 --> 17:40.520
You mean you didn't go in time.

17:40.570 --> 17:41.760
You got something you want to say?

17:41.810 --> 17:43.360
- No, sir.
- You sure?

17:43.410 --> 17:44.360
Yes, Daddy.

17:44.410 --> 17:45.560
I'm not gonna let that go.

17:45.610 --> 17:47.000
I'm tired of having to explain...

17:47.050 --> 17:48.560
Mr. Mayor, do you have a minute?

17:48.610 --> 17:50.400
For you, two minutes.

17:50.450 --> 17:53.000
You seem a little stressed.
Is everything okay?

17:53.050 --> 17:55.040
Just hosing down the normal brush fires.

17:55.090 --> 17:56.440
Well, this might brighten your day.

17:56.490 --> 17:58.270
We just got confirmation that Mr. Brooks

17:58.320 --> 18:00.410
will here next week for the concrete pour,

18:00.460 --> 18:03.010
and he might even make the
party at the Harris estate.

18:03.060 --> 18:04.650
Are you teasing me, Miss Wu?

18:04.700 --> 18:07.120
Because that's mayoral
abuse, which is a misdemeanor.

18:07.170 --> 18:08.720
And if it isn't, I'll make it one.

18:08.770 --> 18:11.420
I'm looking at his
travel itinerary right here.

18:11.470 --> 18:13.090
I could have emailed that to you,

18:13.140 --> 18:14.320
but Mr. Brooks wants to talk

18:14.370 --> 18:16.160
to Judge Harris before he arrives.

18:16.210 --> 18:17.260
We've been calling, but we haven't

18:17.310 --> 18:18.530
been able to get hold of him.

18:18.580 --> 18:19.830
I'll make sure Pernell calls him.

18:19.880 --> 18:21.860
- Thank you.
- Could you...

18:21.910 --> 18:23.870
Could you call him right now?

18:23.920 --> 18:25.030
Right this second?

18:25.080 --> 18:26.600
I know he's very busy,

18:26.650 --> 18:29.040
but things like this make Mr. Brooks worry,

18:29.090 --> 18:32.570
so if you could make it a priority...

18:32.620 --> 18:35.040
I'm working against a bit of
a deadline right this second,

18:35.090 --> 18:37.780
but I'll have him call
him, put Mr. Brooks at ease.

18:37.830 --> 18:39.280
Good, because I would love

18:39.330 --> 18:41.480
to spend the next few days
deciding what dress to wear

18:41.530 --> 18:43.250
and not wondering if this deal

18:43.300 --> 18:47.160
is going to turn into
a pumpkin at midnight.

18:47.210 --> 18:49.060
Got the message.

18:49.110 --> 18:51.630
Thank you.

18:51.680 --> 18:53.160
Felony.

18:53.210 --> 18:56.870
I'm gonna make it a fucking felony.

18:56.920 --> 18:59.170
So once you checked off

18:59.220 --> 19:01.600
all the things on God's to-do list

19:01.650 --> 19:04.510
and PJ woke up,

19:04.560 --> 19:05.940
then what was supposed to happen?

19:05.990 --> 19:08.080
What do you mean?

19:08.130 --> 19:09.540
Nothing.

19:09.590 --> 19:12.250
We just go back to our lives.

19:12.300 --> 19:13.850
Well, that sounds nice.

19:13.900 --> 19:17.320
What did you imagine the
two of you doing together

19:17.370 --> 19:20.160
once you got him back?

19:20.210 --> 19:23.390
Tell him how much I love him.

19:25.680 --> 19:28.600
I'd hold him in my arms
for as long as I could.

19:30.420 --> 19:33.500
Feel him hugging me back.

19:33.550 --> 19:34.940
Okay,

19:34.990 --> 19:37.810
but more than a few minutes
of that would be weird, right?

19:37.860 --> 19:39.570
So then what?

19:39.620 --> 19:43.110
What did you have planned for
after those first few minutes?

19:43.160 --> 19:45.510
I don't know. I don't know.

19:45.560 --> 19:49.980
Life would just go back to being normal.

19:50.030 --> 19:52.690
Tell me about normal.

19:52.740 --> 19:54.560
Hmm?

19:54.610 --> 19:57.790
What did you and PJ used to do together?

20:02.110 --> 20:03.800
Well...

20:05.620 --> 20:07.740
When he was eight,

20:07.790 --> 20:11.640
I got him these walkie-talkies
with a Morse code button,

20:11.690 --> 20:15.240
and we hung a sheet alongside the bunk bed,

20:15.290 --> 20:17.810
pretended it was a submarine.

20:17.860 --> 20:22.780
We used to send coded
messages to each other.

20:22.830 --> 20:25.190
When he was 11,

20:25.240 --> 20:27.990
he figured out how to boost the signal,

20:28.040 --> 20:29.920
have it go across the whole house.

20:29.970 --> 20:31.690
So when PJ woke up,

20:31.740 --> 20:34.730
you were gonna play submarines?

20:36.780 --> 20:40.270
I'm not saying that that's
what we were gonna...

20:40.320 --> 20:43.140
All I'm saying is that
we did do things together.

20:43.190 --> 20:44.510
That's when he was a kid,

20:44.560 --> 20:46.740
when he depended upon you for survival.

20:46.790 --> 20:49.780
Oh, trust me, he still
depends on me for survival.

20:49.830 --> 20:52.850
Who do you think's paying
for that house he lives in?

20:52.900 --> 20:55.180
So it's your fault, then,

20:55.230 --> 20:57.190
that PJ shot himself?

20:57.240 --> 20:58.320
What the hell did you just say?

20:58.370 --> 20:59.990
You just told me that PJ

21:00.040 --> 21:01.660
depended on you for survival.

21:01.710 --> 21:04.390
Sounds to me like you
fucked that up pretty good.

